The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

NATION BRIEFS

 Mumbai, Feb. 6 (PTI): A court today sentenced the president of the Dance Bar Owners Association, Manjeet Singh Sethi, and his son to 10 years rigorous imprisonment for kidnapping and assaulting a court clerk in January 1997.

 They have also been ordered to pay a fine of Rs 1.25 lakh each.

 Sethi and his son were found guilty of kidnapping Kuldip Singh Chandok on January 6, 1997. They later assaulted Chandok with belts and sticks before snatching stamp papers on a property from him. 

 New York (PTI): Sandeep Patel, an immigrant from India who was paralysed neck down since he was shot in a racially-motivated attack in 2000 in Pittsburg, has died of pneumonia. The 32-year-old was the sole survivor of the shooting in which five were killed by Richard Baumhammers, a white man, who said minorities had no right to live in the US.

 Kannur (PTI): The headmaster of a primary school has been arrested on charges of sexually harassing an 11-year-old girl at her home in Kannur, Kerala. K.C. Bhaskaran allegedly tried to molest her while giving her tuition, the girls mother complained.

 Bangalore (PTI): The first light combat aircraft, Tejas, from a limited series production has successfully made a ground run here. The indigenous fighter jet behaved very well as per the specifications, a HAL statement said.

 Panaji (PTI): Around 500 college students have been arrested for staging a two-hour sit-in on the main road linking the Goan capital to the rest of the state. The students claimed the Congress government was failing to implement the Cyberage scheme. The scheme, launched in the earlier BJP regime, promises a computer to college students against a nominal Rs 1,000 from them.




